pageContext.claim: “If elected, Biden will delay the therapies. Look, – I mean, even the vaccines, they're trying to say, oh, it's no good if Trump hasn't it. It's being done by Johnson & Johnson, Pfizer. They – I don't even know who these people are, right? If it comes out with Trump, – how bad is that? They are willing to demean a vaccine for political purposes.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no evidence that the development of a vaccine was delayed for political reasons or because of the election. Ironically, the process went faster than expected because the U.S. caseload was so high.
